TdescFragTag.name: AT_BIRTH_TESTS
TdescFragTag.description: Tests to run between the pregnant sim and their partner, at the time of birth. If any test fails, the the partner sim will not be set as the other parent. This is intended to prevent modifications to the partner sim during the time between impregnation and birth that would make the partner sim an invalid parent (age too young, relationship incestuous, etc).

Tunable.name: BIRTHPARENT_BIT
Tunable.description: The bit that is added on the relationship from the Sim to any of its offspring.

Tunable.name: GENDER_CHANCE_STAT
Tunable.description: A commodity that determines the chance that an offspring is female. The minimum value guarantees the offspring is male, whereas the maximum value guarantees it is female.

Tunable.name: MONOZYGOTIC_OFFSPRING_CHANCE
Tunable.description: The chance that each subsequent offspring of a multiple birth has the same genetics as the first offspring.

TunableList.name: MULTIPLE_OFFSPRING_CHANCES
TunableList.description: A list defining the probabilities of multiple births.

TunableTuple.name: modifiers
TunableTuple.description: A tunable list of test sets and associated multipliers to apply to the total chance of this number of potential offspring.

Tunable.name: base_value
Tunable.description: The basic value to return if no modifications are applied.

TunableList.name: multipliers
TunableList.description: A list of multipliers to apply to base_value.

Tunable.name: multiplier
Tunable.description: The multiplier to apply to base_value if the associated tests pass.

TdescFragTag.name: tests
TdescFragTag.description: A series of tests that must pass in order for multiplier to be applied.

TunableTuple.name: npc_dialog
TunableTuple.description:
A dialog displayed when a NPC Sim gives birth to an offspring that was conceived by a currently player-controlled Sim. The dialog is specifically used when this number of offspring is generated.
Three tokens are passed in: the two parent Sims and the offspring

TunableVariant.name: additional_texts
TunableVariant.description: If enabled, add additional text to the dialog

Tunable.description: A localized string that may use tokens.

Tunable.name: anonymous_target_sim
Tunable.description: If this dialog is using a target sim id to give a conversation type view and this is checked, then the target sim icon will instead be replaced by an anonymous caller.

TunableVariant.name: audio_sting
TunableVariant.description: If enabled, play an audio sting when the dialog is shown.

Tunable.name: audio
Tunable.description: The sound to play.

Tunable.name: immediate_audio
Tunable.description:
If checked, this audio will be triggered immediately, nothing will block.
ex. Earbuds audio will be played immediately while the Sim is routing or animating.

TunableVariant.name: joint_name_hash
TunableVariant.description: Specify if the audio is attached to a slot and, if so, which slot. Otherwise the audio will be attached to the object's origin.

Tunable.name: enabled
Tunable.description: The name of the slot this audio is attached to.

Tunable.name: play_on_active_sim_only
Tunable.description:
If enabled, and audio target is Sim, the audio will only be played on selected Sim. Otherwise it will be played regardless Sim is selected or not.
If audio target is Object, always set this to False. Otherwise the audio will never be played.
ex. This will be useful for Earbuds where we want to hear the music only when the Sim is selected.

TunableList.name: trait_entries
TunableList.description: Sets of traits that might be randomly applied to each generated offspring. Each group is individually randomized.

TunableTuple.description: A set of random traits. Specify a chance that a trait from the group is selected, and then specify a set of traits. Only one trait from this group may be selected. If the chance is less than 100%, no traits could be selected.

Tunable.name: chance
Tunable.description: The chance that a trait from this set is selected.

TunableList.name: traits
TunableList.description: The set of traits that might be applied to each generated offspring. Specify a weight for each trait compared to other traits in the same set.

TunableTuple.description: A weighted trait that might be applied to the generated offspring. The weight is relative to other entries within the same set.

Tunable.name: trait

Tunable.name: weight
Tunable.description: The relative weight of this trait compared to other traits within the same set.

TunableList.name: PREGNANCY_ORIGIN_TRAIT_MAPPING
TunableList.description: A mapping from PregnancyOrigin to a set of traits to be added at the start of the pregnancy, and removed at the end of the pregnancy.

TunableTuple.name: value
TunableTuple.description: A tuple of the traits that should be added/removed with a pregnancy that has this origin, and the content pack they are associated with.

TunableEnum.name: pack
TunableEnum.description: The content pack associated with this set of traits. If the pack is uninstalled, the pregnancy will be auto-completed.

Tunable.name: PREGNANCY_RATE
Tunable.description: The rate per Sim minute of pregnancy.

Tunable.name: PREGNANCY_TRAIT
